# OWNER-REPORTS — non-authoritative

Files under `OWNER-REPORTS/` (including any nested or archived copies kept for history or investigation) are **mostly per-session or short program workfiles**: audits, gap inventories, checklists, and operator notes produced while executing a scope.

## Do not treat as SSOT

- **Not** authoritative product law, API contracts, security baselines, or normative journey definitions.
- **Not** a substitute for code, `END-GOAL-PROJECT.md`, `PROJECT_USER_JOURNEY_STEPS.md`, or **Accepted ADRs** in `ADR/`.

## Allowed use

- **Context** for what was discussed or scoped in a past session; **history** or investigation pointers; **temporary** tracking until work lands in code, ADRs, or the supreme product file above.

## When describing requirements

Prefer **code + formal SSOT** (end-goal doc, journey doc, ADRs). If you mention an owner report, frame it as **historical / working notes**, not “the spec says”.

```markdown
# ❌ BAD — cites owner report as law
Per OWNER-REPORTS/066_*.txt, production must …

# ✅ GOOD — SSOT first, owner report optional
Per END-GOAL-PROJECT.md and ADR 0014 … (066 inventory was a working gap list during closure.)
```
